wikipedia_page.main: John Joseph Curtis (13 December 1888 – 8 March 1955) was an English professional football outside left who played in the Football League for Sunderland, Gainsborough Trinity, Tottenham Hotspur, Fulham, Stockport County and Middlesbrough. He is best remembered for his four-year spell with Tottenham Hotspur between 1909 and 1913.
